President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. called President-elect Gustavo Petro to congratulate him and Vice President-elect Francia Marquez on their election in Colombia. President Biden praised the Colombian people for conducting free and fair elections and expressed U.S. support for Colombia. He emphasized his commitment to working with the President-elect on various areas of cooperation, such as climate change, health security, and the implementation of the 2016 Peace Accord. President Biden also expressed his willingness to discuss bilateral security and counternarcotics cooperation. Both leaders emphasized the importance of mutual respect and partnership in the U.S.-Colombia relationship and agreed to have their teams follow up and engage directly on shared interests.